    "f (v) Compared to steady-state DBM, time-dependent DBM compresses the system's behavior description ability from all (infinite) kinetic moments of to a finite set.",
    "The gain in the system's behavior description ability is that the time span of the behavior is amplified infinitely from 0.",
    "However, there is a trade-off involved in this.",
    "The gain is \"mesoscopic\" and the cost is also \"mesoscopic\".",
    "Both types of DBMs are typical representatives of \"choosing something to do\" or \"doing something and abandoning the others\"."
  ],
